node.title: NT records no new COVID cases as lockout restrictions extended
node.alt: A grey sphere with red and orange blotches.
node.description: The Chief Minister says the Northern Territory recorded no new cases of coronavirus overnight.Â
node.content: ["The Northern Territory has recorded no new cases of coronavirus, according to Chief Minister Michael Gunner.", "But a\u00a0lockout in Greater Darwin, scheduled to end at midnight tonight,\u00a0has been extended to midnight on\u00a0Monday.", "The lockdown currently in place in Katherine will be scaled back to a lockout at 3pm today.", "Mr Gunner said Katherine would exit the lockout along with Darwin at midnight on Monday \"if all goes well\".", "The restrictions were announced by the NT government on Thursday\u00a0after\u00a0an unvaccinated man in his 20s tested positive.", "Mr Gunner said the rules of the lockout in Katherine would be exactly the same as in Darwin.", "\"If you\u2019re fully vaccinated you can go about life as normal as long as you are masked,\" he said.", "\"If you aren\u2019t fully vaccinated you can only leave home for one of five reasons deemed essential.\"", "More to come."]
